From: msedek <msedek@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Mar 2026
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] backends/drm: force modeset on HDMI hotplug for link
 re-training

When an HDMI connector receives a hotplug "change" event but its status
remains "connected" (common with force-enabled connectors or TVs that
switch inputs without electrically disconnecting), the HDMI link may
have degraded. The sink (TV) may have stopped listening to TMDS signals
and needs link re-training when it returns to the HDMI input.

Currently, KWin only forces a modeset when link-status is explicitly
reported as "Bad" by the kernel driver. However, many drivers (notably
NVIDIA) do not set link-status to Bad in this scenario — they report
the forced status and move on.

This patch adds two mechanisms:
1. DrmConnector::isHdmi() accessor to identify HDMI connector types
2. In DrmGpu::updateOutputs(), when a connected HDMI connector already
   has an active output, set m_forceModeset to trigger link re-training
   via the existing modeset pipeline.

This is gated behind a new parameter to updateOutputs() that tracks
whether the call originated from a hotplug event, preventing unnecessary
modesets during initial scan or session resume.

The modeset to the same mode is safe — it only re-trains the TMDS link
and re-negotiates HDCP, with at most a brief blanking period.

BUG: https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=XXXXX
Signed-off-by: msedek <msedek@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 src/backends/drm/drm_backend.cpp   |  6 ++++--
 src/backends/drm/drm_connector.cpp |  7 +++++++
 src/backends/drm/drm_connector.h   |  1 +
 src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.cpp       | 18 +++++++++++++++++-
 src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.h         |  2 +-
 5 files changed, 30 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.h b/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.h
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.h
+++ b/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.h
@@ -63,6 +63,7 @@ public:
     bool isConnected() const;
     bool isNonDesktop() const;
     bool isInternal() const;
+    bool isHdmi() const;

     const Edid *edid() const;
     QString connectorName() const;
diff --git a/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.cpp b/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.cpp
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.cpp
+++ b/src/backends/drm/drm_connector.cpp
@@ -181,6 +181,13 @@ bool DrmConnector::isConnected() const
     return !m_driverModes.empty() && m_conn && m_conn->connection == DRM_MODE_CONNECTED;
 }

+bool DrmConnector::isHdmi() const
+{
+    return m_conn &&
+           (m_conn->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_HDMIA ||
+            m_conn->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_HDMIB);
+}
+
 QString DrmConnector::connectorName() const
 {
     const char *connectorName = drmModeGetConnectorTypeName(m_conn->connector_type);
diff --git a/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.h b/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.h
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.h
+++ b/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.h
@@ -113,7 +113,7 @@ public:

     void setEglDisplay(std::unique_ptr<EglDisplay> &&display);

-    bool updateOutputs();
+    bool updateOutputs(bool fromHotplug = false);
     void removeOutputs();

     DrmPipeline::Error testPendingConfiguration();
diff --git a/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.cpp b/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.cpp
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.cpp
+++ b/src/backends/drm/drm_gpu.cpp
@@ -249,7 +249,7 @@ void DrmGpu::initDrmResources()
     }
 }

-bool DrmGpu::updateOutputs()
+bool DrmGpu::updateOutputs(bool fromHotplug)
 {
     if (!m_isActive) {
         return false;
@@ -336,6 +336,22 @@ bool DrmGpu::updateOutputs()
             }
+            /*
+             * When a hotplug event arrives for an HDMI connector that is
+             * still connected with an active output, force a modeset to
+             * re-train the TMDS link. This handles the case where a TV
+             * switches to built-in apps (Netflix, etc.) and stops
+             * listening on its HDMI receiver. When the TV returns to the
+             * HDMI input, the GPU needs to re-negotiate the link even
+             * though the connector status never changed.
+             */
+            if (fromHotplug && conn->isConnected() && conn->isHdmi() && findOutput(conn->id())) {
+                if (!m_forceModeset) {
+                    qCDebug(KWIN_DRM, "HDMI hotplug on connected connector %s, "
+                            "forcing modeset for link re-training",
+                            qPrintable(conn->connectorName()));
+                    m_forceModeset = true;
+                }
+            }
             it++;
         } else {
diff --git a/src/backends/drm/drm_backend.cpp b/src/backends/drm/drm_backend.cpp
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/src/backends/drm/drm_backend.cpp
+++ b/src/backends/drm/drm_backend.cpp
@@ -218,7 +218,9 @@ void DrmBackend::handleUdevEvent()
             if (gpu && gpu->isActive()) {
                 qCDebug(KWIN_DRM) << "Received change event for monitored drm device" << gpu->drmDevice()->path();
-                updateOutputs();
+                for (auto it = m_gpus.begin(); it != m_gpus.end(); ++it) {
+                    (*it)->updateOutputs(true);
+                }
+                Q_EMIT outputsQueried();
             }
         }
     }
